Download Debian for Virtualbox
- https://www.debian.org/distrib/netinst > Small CDs or USB sticks > amd64

Settings Virtual Machine
- right click machine
- Settings > Advanced
- Shared Clipboard > Bidirectional / Drag'n'Drop > Bidirectional
- System > Motherboard > Boot Order > Optical & Hard Disk
- Storage > Controller: IDE > Empty > Optical Drive: IDE Secondary Master > click CD.DVD Symbol > Choose Virtual Optical Disk File > Select Downloaded File: debian-8.6.0-amd64-netinst.iso > Open
- Network > Adapter 1 > Enable Network Adapter > Bridged Adapter
- Ok

Start Machine & Install Debian
- Graphical install
- Language: English
- Origin: other > Netherlands
- Keyboard: American English
- debian8
- Domain Name: 4everCollect.com
- Root password
- myname
- myname
- User password
- Time Zone
- Guided - use entire disk
- All files in one partition
- Finish partitioning and write changes to disk
- Write the changes to disk: yes
- Mirror Country: Closest Country
- Debian archive mirror: Try picking the best
- HTTP proxy information: Leave blank
- Participate in survey: no
- Software to install: print server & SSH server & standard system utilities
- Install Grub boot loader: yes
- Device for boot loader installation: /dev/sda
- Installation Complete

Log in

- Wait for terminal
- type: su -
- type: password
- type: apt-get install build-essential module-assistant linux-headers-$(uname -r)
- type: Y
